Don’t mess with your colleagues.
If you know in advance that you’re not going to go to the office the next day, or there might be something that makes you have to stay at home, signal it so that your colleagues and boss don’t face your absence the next day.
Bumping, giggling, phone calls
Have you gotten into work, but are you rudely drawn out of it by the giggles of your colleagues?
Have you inadvertently witnessed a telephone conversation that would have been better not to have been heard?
Do not disturb your coworkers with buzzing, singing, loud talking (which you do above their heads), or with beating feet, constant swearing, or loud dissatisfaction.
These can all be confusing, even if they are not immersed in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Do you blame others for your mistakes?
